As the clock ticks fast to the 2023 general elections, six governorship aspirants from various political parties are expected to battle for delegates to grab their respective party tickets ahead of Yobe State gubernatorial election. These include the incumbent Governor of Yobe State Mai Mala Buni (APC), Umar Ali (APC), Sheriff Abdullahi (PDP), Ali Adamu Tikau (PDP), Abba Gana Tata (PDP) and Ya’u Sabo (AA). Yobe State governorship has since 1999 been to All People’s Party (APP), All Nigeria People’s Party (ANPP) and All Progressives Congress (APC). -Advertisement- The state has three senatorial districts of zone ‘A’ comprising Damaturu, Gujba, Gulani, Geidam, Yunusari and Tarmuwa local government areas while zone ‘B’ is made up of Fune, Fika Potiskum and Nangere whereas zone ‘C’ has Jakusko, Bade, Nguru, Machina, Karasuwa and Yusufari respectively. Between 2019 to date, the state is enjoying relative peace which according to experts will enable free levelling ground for the people to exercise their civil rights of voting. Consultations and meetings have begun by these governorship aspirants and others vying for elective offices in the state.